  "content": [
    {
      "id": "block_1",
      "type": "text",
      "latex": "Soit $f \\colon \\R^2 \\to \\R$,\n$$ (x,y) \\mapsto \\dfrac{x^2 y^2}{x^2 y^2 + (x-y)^2} $$",
      "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f \\colon \\R^2 \\to \\R\\)</span>,\n<span class=\"math display\">\\[(x,y) \\mapsto \\dfrac{x^2 y^2}{x^2 y^2 + (x-y)^2}\\]</span></p>",
      "order": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "block_2",
      "type": "question",
      "latex": "Donner l'ensemble de définition de $f$.",
      "html": "<p>Donner l’ensemble de définition de <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f\\)</span>.</p>",
      "order": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "block_3",
      "type": "reponse",
      "latex": "La fonction $f$ est définie pour tout $(x,y)\\in \\R^2$ tels que $x^2 y^2 + (x-y)^2 \\neq 0 $. Or $x^2y^2 + (x-y)^2 = 0 \\iff xy = 0 \\text{ et } x=y \\iff x=y=0$ donc $f$ est définie sur $\\R^2 \\backslash \\{(0,0)\\}$.",
      "html": "<p>La fonction <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f\\)</span> est définie pour tout <span class=\"math inline\">\\((x,y)\\in \\R^2\\)</span> tels que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x^2 y^2 + (x-y)^2 \\neq 0\\)</span>. Or <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x^2y^2 + (x-y)^2 = 0 \\iff xy = 0 \\text{ et } x=y \\iff x=y=0\\)</span> donc <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f\\)</span> est définie sur <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\R^2 \\backslash \\{(0,0)\\}\\)</span>.</p>",
      "order": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "block_4",
      "type": "question",
      "latex": "Pour $x$ fixé, calculer $g(x) = \\lim\\limits_{y \\to 0} f(x,y)$.",
      "html": "<p>Pour <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x\\)</span> fixé, calculer <span class=\"math inline\">\\(g(x) = \\lim\\limits_{y \\to 0} f(x,y)\\)</span>.</p>",
      "order": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "block_5",
      "type": "reponse",
      "latex": "Soit $x \\in \\R$ : si $x=0$, $f(0,y) = 0$ et si $x \\neq 0$, $f(x,y) \\xrightarrow[y \\to 0]{} \\frac{0}{x^2} = 0$",
      "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x \\in \\R\\)</span> : si <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x=0\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f(0,y) = 0\\)</span> et si <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x \\neq 0\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f(x,y) \\xrightarrow[y \\to 0]{} \\frac{0}{x^2} = 0\\)</span></p>",
      "order": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "block_6",
      "type": "question",
      "latex": "Pour $y$ fixé, calculer $h(y) = \\lim\\limits_{x \\to 0} f(x,y)$.",
      "html": "<p>Pour <span class=\"math inline\">\\(y\\)</span> fixé, calculer <span class=\"math inline\">\\(h(y) = \\lim\\limits_{x \\to 0} f(x,y)\\)</span>.</p>",
      "order": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "block_7",
      "type": "reponse",
      "latex": "De même, $h(y) = 0$.",
      "html": "<p>De même, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(h(y) = 0\\)</span>.</p>",
      "order": 7
    },
    {
      "id": "block_8",
      "type": "question",
      "latex": "Calculer $\\lim\\limits_{x \\to 0} g(x)$.",
      "html": "<p>Calculer <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\lim\\limits_{x \\to 0} g(x)\\)</span>.</p>",
      "order": 8
    },
    {
      "id": "block_9",
      "type": "reponse",
      "latex": "On en déduit que $\\lim\\limits_{x \\to 0} g(x) = 0$",
      "html": "<p>On en déduit que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\lim\\limits_{x \\to 0} g(x) = 0\\)</span></p>",
      "order": 9
    },
    {
      "id": "block_10",
      "type": "question",
      "latex": "Calculer $\\lim\\limits_{y \\to 0} h(y)$.",
      "html": "<p>Calculer <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\lim\\limits_{y \\to 0} h(y)\\)</span>.</p>",
      "order": 10
    },
    {
      "id": "block_11",
      "type": "reponse",
      "latex": "De même $\\lim\\limits_{y \\to 0} h(y) = 0$",
      "html": "<p>De même <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\lim\\limits_{y \\to 0} h(y) = 0\\)</span></p>",
      "order": 11
    },
    {
      "id": "block_12",
      "type": "question",
      "latex": "La fonction $f$ admet-elle une limite quand $(x,y) \\to (0,0)$~?",
      "html": "<p>La fonction <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f\\)</span> admet-elle une limite quand <span class=\"math inline\">\\((x,y) \\to (0,0)\\)</span> ?</p>",
      "order": 12
    },
    {
      "id": "block_13",
      "type": "reponse",
      "latex": "Non car $f(x,x) = 1 \\xrightarrow[x \\to 0]{} 1$ et $f(x,0) = 0 \\xrightarrow[x \\to 0]{} 0 \\neq 1$ : on a deux chemins qui donnent deux limites différentes.",
      "html": "<p>Non car <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f(x,x) = 1 \\xrightarrow[x \\to 0]{} 1\\)</span> et <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f(x,0) = 0 \\xrightarrow[x \\to 0]{} 0 \\neq 1\\)</span> : on a deux chemins qui donnent deux limites différentes.</p>",
      "order": 13
    }
  ],
